HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 288
By Marsh
A RESOLUTION to congratulate Bruce MacDonald and his horse
Cavender, the eighty-sixth Tennessee Walking
Horse National Celebration World Grand
Champion.
WHEREAS, the Tennessee Walking Horse National Celebration in Shelbyville is the
premier event for the Tennessee Walking Horse industry, showcasing these magnificent horses
and crowning the breed's World Grand Champion; and
WHEREAS, Bruce MacDonald and his horse Cavender, by a unanimous selection of the
judge panel, captured the 2024 World Grand Championship at the eighty-sixth annual
Tennessee Walking Horse National Celebration; and
WHEREAS, no stranger to success, Bruce MacDonald had a prosperous business
career with franchises for Cummins diesel engines and Carrier Transicold; after Mr. MacDonald
and his wife raised their two sons, Mrs. MacDonald thought it time to return to her love of
horses, and together, the couple captured success in the show ring; and
WHEREAS, Cavender was trained and ridden to victory by Tim Smith, who first spotted
the smooth moving, high-headed colt at the Abernathy Colt Preview in Mississippi in 2021; and
WHEREAS, Bruce MacDonald moved quickly and purchased the horse; his wife, Robin
MacDonald, named the colt Cavender, an Irish name, meaning someone who is bold or brave,
and Brenda Corey raised him under the direction of Cottonwood Farm; and
WHEREAS, as time went on, Cavender was a winner each time he entered the show
ring, earning blue ribbons at the ThorSport Spring Fling in Murfreesboro and the Spring Fun
Show in Shelbyville; and
